item.description:
ansible&rsquo;s &quot;&ndash;extra-vars&quot; is the option to pass variables from command line. In using packer with ansible, you can still specify &ldquo;&ndash;extra-vars&rdquo; through packer&rsquo;s &ldquo;extra_arguments&rdquo;. Here&rsquo;some example.
 ansible  We consider the case that we specify parameter &ldquo;base_ami&rdquo;, &ldquo;parameter_1&rdquo;, and &ldquo;parameter_2&rdquo; for ansible. {% raw %}
$ cat sample.yml - hosts: sample roles: sample_dir vars: base_ami: &#39;{{ base_ami }}&#39; parameter_1: &#39;{{ parameter_1 }}&#39; parameter_2: &#39;{{ parameter_2 }}&#39; {% endraw %}
